            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-4">Currently, tourists can easily travel by air, train or public transportation connecting to areas of Japan to visit, explore culture and beauty in all parts of Japan. areas across the country such as Hokkaido, Honshu, Shikoku, Kyushu to the tropical thousand-island archipelago including Okinawa island.... Japan is a country with a fairly evenly distributed terrain with famous large mountain ranges such as Mount Fuji, waterfalls, hot springs, endless coastal roads and clean air cities. , clean. To visit this civilized country, we should not be subjective, there may be just a small mistake and your chance to come to Japan may be slower than planned. The following are shared tips for traveling to Japan that you should know when visiting the land of the rising sun.</p>
            <p class="handbook-title-1 mt-3">Apply for a visa to Japan</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2">Applying for a visa to Japan is easy, but it will be difficult for those who have not carefully prepared their visa application documents. If you want to go smoothly in the visa application process, please prepare the following basic documents completely according to the instructions of the Japanese embassy.</p>
