            <p class="handbook-title-1 mt-3">Suitable time to travel</p>
            <img src="~/Content/Images/Home/Handbook/Japan/japan-1.jpg" width="100%" />
            <p class="note-img">Japan in spring</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2">Japan is in a temperate zone, with four distinct seasons. Tourists can visit Japan in any season of the year. However, the time period when many tourists choose to tour Japan is in the fall and spring.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Spring in Japan</b> is an ideal travel time for visitors. Why is now the time for you to travel? First, spring weather in Japan is warm and sunny and the air is no longer humid like winter. The scenery here is also proportional to the weather. The trees sprout and grow lushly, and it's cherry blossom season.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Summer</b> starts from April to the end of June. April is the time when most tourists visit Japan because this time the climate conditions are best with sunshine and pleasant temperatures. May is considered a tourism month with many festivals taking place in all parts of the country. In June, the weather is still nice for those who want to explore the scenery cooled by the rain.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Autumn in Japan</b> also has similarities with the weather of Vietnam. July with sudden rains. The fall of August is ready with many changes in the color of maple leaves from green to red, similar to the spreading effect of cherry blossoms blooming in spring., festivals such as the Hitachi Seaside Park flower festival – Ibaraki, or traditional mid-autumn festival,…. September is quiet with rain, many storms are forecast to land in some areas such as Okinawa, Kyushu and Shikoku. But luckily, these storms did not affect the beautiful scenery of Japan.</p>
            <img src="~/Content/Images/Home/Handbook/Japan/japan-2.jpg" width="100%" />
            <p class="note-img">Japan in autumn</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Winter</b>: In Japan, it can be said that late January to February is the time when the weather is at its coldest. The Osaka region is an area with quite warm temperatures compared to other areas because up to this point there has been almost no snowfall, while in the North of Japan, snow has covered every road. For those who love skiing, this is the ideal time to participate in skiing.</p>

            <p class="handbook-title-1 mt-3">Choose plane tickets to Japan</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2">Nowadays, the aviation industry is very developed, so traveling between countries is no longer as difficult as before. And there are also many flights from major airports such as Noi Bai and Tan Son Nhat to Japan. You can also choose for yourself cheap air tickets from airlines such as Vietnam Airline, China Southern Airline, Philippine Airline, Singapore Airline, Silkair,...</p>

            <p class="handbook-title-1 mt-3">Move</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2">When it comes to Japan, visitors absolutely do not have to measure quality or move from one place to another. The low-cost airline system makes it simple for international tourists to visit the land of cherry blossoms. The train, subway, and bus systems are also options for international tourists as well as local people as a popular means of transportation. When traveling to Japan, you can choose any means of transportation. But remember to exclude taxis if you want to have an economical trip, because taxis in Japan are among the most expensive in Asia.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2">If you want to travel in the inner city, you can choose to travel by subway. In Tokyo, you have Tokyo Metro with prices from 160 JPY and Toei line with prices from 170 JPY. Paying for public transportation: visitors can pay in cash, buy tickets at train ticket stations, use ID cards purchased at card sales stations, or alternatively pay by pre-paying accommodation. automatic ticket vending machine. Choosing to pay using an ID card is the most cost-effective and most usable way. Traveling by bus is quite similar to Vietnam. Tourists should determine their destination, route and choose the appropriate bus route. The subway is the means of transportation chosen by many tourists because it is cheap, very modern, and makes travel quick and easy.</p>

            <p class="handbook-title-1 mt-3">Hotel and leisure services in Japan</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2">If you have the opportunity to travel to Japan, you never have to worry about hotels, resorts or any services. When you choose to book a room, please note, book as early as possible during the red leaf season and cherry blossom season. The best way is to use online booking websites like agoda. Or consult some professional travel agencies, because they know best about cheap hotels in Japan.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2">Japan travel experience on how to book a room is that you should choose hotels and motels close to bus and subway stations for convenient travel. In addition, visitors can also choose traditional Japanese-style hotels to experience some of their traditional culture.</p>


            <p class="handbook-title-1 mt-3">Tourist attractions not to be missed when traveling to Japan</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Mount Fuji or Mount Fuji</b> located on the island of Honshu is the highest mountain in Japan with an altitude of 3,776.24 above sea level, the 2nd highest peak on an island in Asia and the 7th highest in the world. This is an inactive stratovolcano with its last eruption in 1707-1708.</p>
